### EUROCAE ED-254 - Arrival Sequence Service Performance Standard

**Title**: EUROCAE ED-254 - Arrival Sequence Service Performance Standard

**Edition**: June 2018

**Publisher**: EUROCAE (European Organisation for Civil Aviation Equipment)

**URL**: https://www.eurocae.net/products/ed-254/

**Purpose**: Technical specification defining service interface bindings for **Extended AMAN (Arrival Sequence Service)**.

> **IMPORTANT CLARIFICATION**: ED-254 is specifically for Extended AMAN, **NOT for DNOTAM**.
> For DNOTAM, there is no formal service standard/specification like ED-254. DNOTAM uses the Service Definition from the SWIM Registry.

**Key Coverage** (for AMAN only):
- WS-Light binding (REQ-017254)
- AMQP messaging binding (REQ-0200)
- Service Description Document structure
- Event scenarios and data model mappings
- Payload schema requirements

**What DNOTAM uses instead**:
- SWIM Registry Service Definition: https://eur-registry.swim.aero/services/eurocontrol-digital-notam-subscription-and-request-service-010000
- EUROCONTROL SPEC-170 (Yellow Profile) for protocol requirements

**Citation Format**:
```
EUROCAE, "ED-254: Arrival Sequence Service Performance Standard", June 2018.
```

